                <DIV class="ReviewHeading">Book Description:</DIV>
                <span id="Label1">"This book should be read by anyone concerned about violence-that is, by everyone." <br>-George B. Schaller, author of The Last Panda, The Serengeti Lion, and The Year of the Gorilla  <P>"Michael Ghiglieri takes on a topic-male aggression-that many researchers try to avoid, and he takes it on with honesty, with grace, and with a real sense of hope. And it's a startlingly good read; Ghiglieri is a natural storyteller in addition to being a fine researcher." <br>-Deborah Blum, Pulitzer Prize-winning author of Sex on the Brain</span>
              
